Abstract: At the last minute, Hungary's millennium planners turned into the Not-Ready-for-Prime-Time Players.    Two unusual events had been set for midnight: the first spin of a giant Wheel of Time holding an hourglass containing seven tons of customized sand, and a special session of Parliament to celebrate 1,000 years of Hungarian statehood.
